Coagulate tooling

Coagulate Blood Tooling:

Coagulate blood tooling is a specialized form of blood magic where the internal components of blood are morphed and compressed into solid objects. These items, usually weapons, Armor pieces, or instruments, are formed from the metallic and organic matter naturally found in blood.

While coagulate tools are often lightweight and extremely sharp, they are also notoriously brittle, prone to shattering under repeated stress. Their primary strength lies in magical conductivity and rapid creation, rather than physical endurance.

Blood-Based Variance:

Due to the differing chemical and magical profiles between species' blood types, coagulated tools may carry unique traits such as:

  • Unusual magnetic or conductive properties
  • Reactive edge behaviours
  • Enhanced compatibility with certain spells or glyphs

This makes blood not only a material, but a signature, encoding species-specific quirks into every crafted piece.

Limitations:

  • Fragile under sustained impact
  • Often temporary, and start deteriorating from the point of creation
